  <h1 class="heading-primary align-left flex-center">
    A LEGACY PASSED <br> DOWN GENERATIONS
  </h1>
  <div class="flex-text-first" style="margin-bottom:50px;">
    <div class="flex-content-left">
      <p>Embark on a captivating journey as we unveil the true origins of Estate '98, a tale that dates back two centuries when Manuel Larin family, hailing from Spain, bought the storied lands encircling the majestic Santa Ana Volcano with the name of “Mashcarascuahuit” which means wooden mask in Nahuat (Pipil native language). From that fateful arrival, a legacy took root, steadfastly nurtured and upheld by six generations of growing and cultivating coffee. Today, their unwavering dedication persists, passing down the mantle of excellence with each passing era.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-image manuel-padding">
