    </div>
    <div class="flex-content-right pl-100">
      <p>From the history of this lineage, Roberto Larin emerged as a visionary ahead of his time, propelling the family's coffee enterprise to new heights. His pioneering spirit led to the expansion of wet and dry mill production, igniting a transformative chapter in the Larin family's legacy. Now, Andres and Jose Larin, custodians of this illustrious heritage, build upon their grandfather’s innovations, infusing their own creative ingenuity into the fabric of the family business. Together, they continue to shape the future of Estate '98, breathing life into their ancestral wisdom while forging an indelible path of their own that is steadfastly committed to the pursuit of innovation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flex-image-first">
    <h1 class="santa-title">Santa Ana volcano</h1>
    <div class="flex-content-right">
      <p>Juayua, perched in the mountains around the magnificent Santa Ana volcano in El Salvador, stands as an enduring testament to the monumental significance it holds for coffee production in this land. For generations, this fertile and enchanting land has nurtured coffee plants, bestowing upon them the perfect balance of sun, volcanic soil, and elevation. The Santa Ana volcano and Ilamaptec-Apaneca mountain range, with their majestic presence, not only provides a breathtaking backdrop but also plays a crucial role in shaping the microclimate that ensures the quality and distinct flavor profiles of El Salvador's renowned coffee.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flex-text-first">
